# Machine Learning

 ## 1. AI vs Machine Learnign vs Deep Learning    

![0*Q3PICBlib-932hhH.webp](data:image/webp;base64,)

From https://medium.com/swlh/artificial-intelligence-machine-learning-and-deep-learning-whats-the-real-difference-94fe7e528097

### 1.1 AI
- Make machine to think like human
- To solve some problems, it is based on Algorithms
- Artificial intelligence builds its own rule system in the process of creating algorithmic rules that solve problems.
- It can solve the problems itself

### 1.2 Machine Learning
- To build its own rules, analyze the data provided, and then learn.
- Big data needs because the more data it learns, it has the higher the performance.
- Making judgments and predictions about a problem based on learning

### 1.3 Deep Learning 
- Learning data using information input/output hierarchy similar to neurons in the human brain
- It can learn data itself
- There is a speed difference depending on computer's performance
